content.description: A really fun problem starting on two small huecos up to some scrappy crimp action and tough footwork to surmount a bulge followed by a demanding slopey topout. Full value. Downclimb the rope.
content.protection: Landing is good, but at least a pad is desired, as is a spotter who actually cares about your physical wellbeing.

content.description: Downstream a good ways, just after an especially rickity boardwalk propped up by the root structure of an ancient cypress, you will find a 10-15 foot wall with several very worthy problems on it. Several of these problems either should not top out or top out and are downclimbed with the aid of a rope tied to a tree.
